cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper focuses on the micro-architecture level of GPUs and provides insights into the latency of each instruction executing in the GPU pipeline(s) and the access overhead of the various memory hierarchies found in GPUs. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper aims to help architects and software developers to perform informed optimizations to their applications by providing accurate characterization of the latencies of different GPUs. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the impact of various optimizations that the CUDA compiler can perform over the various latencies. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper provides insights into the performance characteristics of GPUs, which can be useful for system-level optimizations. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on GPUs, which are commonly used for parallel computing, and provides insights into their performance characteristics.
